3. Clustering:

Q 3A. Apply K-Means clustering for 2 to 10 clusters.

Ans 3A

In [22]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from scipy.spatial.distance import cdist
from scipy.stats import zscore

car_attr_split =  car_merg_cln_df.iloc[ :, 1: ]
car_attr_splScald = car_attr_split.apply(zscore)

clusters_rng = range( 2, 11 )
k_meansDistortions = []

for kclus in clusters_rng:
    model = KMeans( n_clusters = kclus)
    model.fit( car_attr_splScald )
    predctns = model.predict( car_attr_splScald )
    k_meansDistortions.append( sum( np.min(cdist( car_attr_splScald, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1 )) / car_attr_splScald.shape[0] )

Q 3B. Plot a visual and find elbow point.

Ans 3B

In [23]:
plt.plot( clusters_rng, k_meansDistortions, 'bx-' )
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average distortion')
plt.title('Choose the optimum k with the Elbow Method ');

Q 3C. In the above visual, highlight which are the possible Elbow points.

Ans 3C

In the above elbow chart the possible elbow points of k value is identified as 5 and 7

Q 3D. . Train a K-means clustering model once again on the optimal number of clusters

Ans 3D. As earlier stated the optimal number clusters to be tried is 5 and 7.

In [24]:
#Using 5 as the cluster number
opt_model_k5 = KMeans( 5 )
opt_model_k5.fit( car_attr_splScald )
opt_prediction_k5 = opt_model_k5.predict( car_attr_splScald )

#Using 7 as the cluster number
opt_model_k7 = KMeans( 7 )
opt_model_k7.fit( car_attr_splScald )
opt_prediction_k7 = opt_model_k7.predict( car_attr_splScald )

5. Data Understanding & Cleaning:

Q 5A. Explain pre-requisite/assumptions of PCA

Ans 5A

  • Linearity

    • Assumes that there is linearity in the data set. Assumes the data is continous.

  • High Variance

    • Assumes that features with larger variance correspond to interesting dynamics and lower ones correspond to noise. The features with high varaince are favoured over the ones with less variance.

  • Outliers

    • The Outliers are either eliminated or normalized

  • Correlation

    • The features should have good co-relation that enables reduce them dimensionally with out altering their perforamnce.

Q 5B. Explain advantages and limitations of PCA

Ans 5B

Advantages

  • Reduces the dataset dimensions to ease of executing the model
  • Improves the peformance of the algorithm
  • Consolidates or removes features that has less impact on the prediction or score
  • Reduces overfitting as more number of features influences over fitting
  • Enables with better vizulaization as features are less

Limitations

  • Transformed principal components is difficult to interpret than the orginal feature
  • Data needs to be standardized before applying PCA.
  • While reducing the principal components some of the key features might be dropped if the data is not properly standardized.
